<div class="section">
	<div class="col span_10_of_10 toppad">
    <div class="center-col-shadow">
      <div class="prof-container">
        <div class="prof">


<div class="user-info-box-container">
  <div class="user-info-box">
    <!-- Here is where the user information will be printed -->
      <div class="prof-pic-container">
        <div class="prof-pic img-circle">

            <%= link_to image_tag("twitter.png", :class => "img-circle prof-pic-pic")%>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="user-info-name">
        <h3>
          <%= @user.firstname %>
          <%= @user.lastname %>
        </h3>
      </div>

      <div class="user-info-school">
        <%= @user.school %>
      </div>

  <!-- just a thought, maybe keep track of how much they have participated? -->

      <div class="user-info-total-debates">
        <% total_debate_instances = @debates.length + @firetalks.length + @firetalk_debaters.length %>
        <%= "Total debates: " + total_debate_instances.to_s %>
      </div>


      <div class="user-info-reset-password">
        <%= session[:user_id].to_s + "Reset Password" + @user.id.to_s %>
        <% if session[:user_id] == @user.id %>
        <%= nav_link("Reset Password", change_password_path, :method => "get") %>
        <% end %>
      </div>

<div class="user-info-about-me">
    Perhaps a user inputted about section of a few paragraphs.
  Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Duis vitae nulla
  posuere, semper ligula eget, pharetra nisl. Suspendisse rutrum ultricies
