  egestas. Curabitur suscipit est ac urna pharetra, sit amet tempus quam
  pretium. Vestibulum eu porta ligula. In massa eros, convallis eu est
  eget, cursus viverra diam. Suspendisse in ligula lectus.
  </div>

  <div class="user-info-connections">
    this will be small (circle?) thumbnails of connected users, with a rollover
    showing their name.
  </div>
</div>
</div>






<!--
Here is all the profile activity ordered by date created
The render method you see is rendering a partial. For every iteration of the loop,
it will render the corresponding partials:
  Firetalk: /firetalks/_firetalk.html.erb
  FiretalkDebater: /firetalk_debaters/_firetalk_debater.html.erb
  and so on for debates and posts
-->
<div class="user-activity-container">


  <div class="user-activity-organizer-container">
    <div class="user-activity-organizer">

organize by: <span style="text-decoration: underline; margin-left:10px;">---    box of options   v   --</span>

    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="user-activity-box">
<% @total.each do |obj| %>
  <% if obj %>
  <div class="user-activity-item-container">
  <div class="user-activity-item">
    <strong>TEST TITLE</strong> <em>debate or ft</em>
</br>
    test topic/minidescription, if won or place (1st,2nd,etc) in debate/firetalk

    <%= render(:partial => obj, :locals => {:obj => obj}) %>

  </div>
</div>
</br>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

</div>
</div>


